    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; DT, 9 and 10 Engine Service Manual - Power Cylinders - Installation
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Installation</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="2">
            <title>Cylinder Sleeve</title>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, if any piston ring or cylinder sleeve is replaced, replace that
                        cylinder sleeve and piston rings as a set.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>If required, install appropriate shim(s) in each crankcase counterbore based on
                        <hotlnk document="eges3351_381.xml" xrefid="s1518">counterbore depth measurements</hotlnk>
                        <xref refid="s1518"/>.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If required, install shim(s) in each crankcase counterbore to bring cylinder sleeve
                    protrusion within
                    <hotlnk document="eges3351_T335001501.xml" xrefid="t335001501">Specifications</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="t335001501"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f3350015481" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figh06/H06070.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Cylinder sleeve and crevice seal</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Each cylinder sleeve has one crevice seal.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lightly lubricate crevice seal with clean engine oil and install in cylinder sleeve
                    groove. Make sure crevice seal is properly aligned in the cylinder sleeve groove.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Apply clean engine oil to the lower crankcase counterbore and crevice seal bore.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f3350015482" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg7/EG7219.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Cylinder sleeve installation</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Carefully install each cylinder sleeve in its crankcase counterbore.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">After installation,
                    <hotlnk document="eges3351_382.xml" xrefid="s1519">Measure Cylinder Sleeve Protrusion</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="s1519"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Measure cylinder sleeve protrusion at three locations evenly spaced around each cylinder
                    sleeve. If the difference of the three measurements for any one cylinder is greater then (0.001 in)
                    check for an improperly aligned crevice seal and re-measure protrusion.
                </para>
                <para>Average the three measurements and check cylinder sleeve protrusion
                    <hotlnk document="eges3351_T335001501.xml" xrefid="t335001501">Specification</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="t335001501"/>. If required, determine shim thickness necessary to meet the cylinder
                    sleeve protrusion specification.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
